76561198024972696,Recommended,259740,16608041,"Posted: 21 June, 2015",all,DALCOhstangultion,"I'm very close to starting to NOT recommend these Artifex Mundi casual point-and-click adventrure Hidden Object Games (HOG).  It's nothing particular to this ""Nightmares from the Deep: The Cursed Heart"" game.  It's more of a recurring motif problem.  To wit, their Achievements combined with the inability to either save a game or just plain quit a game and start over.  In this case, I'd made my first run through on Casual and doing the HOGs.  So, I started up another run on Expert and was working on the Mahjong games in place of the HOGs.  About a quarter of the game in, I realized I'd just done a HOG instead of a Majong (i.e., I'd messed up the Achievement).  Without a way to restore a save or just quit and start over, I'd have to finish the entire game knowing I couldn't get the Achievement and restart another run.  No.  Not gonna happen.  So, I'm upset, frustrated, and uninstalling the game.Now, as to the game itself, it's a little below par for Artifex Mundi.  For some reason, it's a bit hard to see the objects in the HOGs.  Also, there are a lot of cases where you get stuck, only to realized that a HOG has popped up somewhere on the map that you'd otherwise have no reason to re-visit.  If a HOG re-activates like that, there should be a quest type of task that would take you back to the area to see the now-active HOG.  And, finally, the voice work (heck, even the role) of the protagonist's daughter is really annoying.Other than that, it's pretty much a standard Artifiex Mundi HOG (decent graphics, mostly tolerable voice acting, and reasonable puzzles).  I got about 3.6 hours out of my first run.  If I'd gone on to continue the last run, I'd probably have gotten about 5-1/2 to 6 hours of ""enjoyment"" out of it.  So, if you decide to buy it, I'd suggest getting it on sale."
